column5: Awesome. Missed bass opener. Stuck working the next two weeks because my boss took a holiday. Just had to leave for the opener! Anyone think the rain might hold off tomorrow. Considering scugog or cooks bay tomorrow during the day
Great morning to be out. Nicely done Terry, you'll get them next time Brian.
Hey he got more bass than me! (and a nice soup I might add )
Nice job. Was an awesome morning on Simcoe. We had the same results - boated over 20 by lunch. Most came right out from the grass. Fantastic opener

Im not going to say much,except,I suck.  This guy on the other hand,was putting on a clinic.Believe his number was 10/16.I stopped counting.  I cant believe I got smacked down. Losing my touch I guess.            Lets just say,the bass gods are against me,for turning to the dark side.  Hopefull things will change when we go smallie hunting buddy.. Thanks for the morning out.
Lets see some fly rod Bass, you havnt turned to the dark side, just the elitist side
It looks like you were stuck in the back of the boat Brian, silly you.  Good stuff Terry and way to go keeping Brian at the back of the boat.
See? Sometimes you can learn things fishing with old folks, even if they school you. LOL Mr. T wins?
it was great to be out doing some bass'n again  ]  it's too bad we didn't get a photo of that snapping turtle
Yep back of the boat can be tough. Usually gotta go with a curveball.
I did make a flip out in front of the boat,but the guy up front,flipped out.
Looks like Terry kicked yer butt there B  Looks like you at least got one.  Where's your sign bud  Nice day to be out there by the looks of it
Plenty of time.
Not at the rate yer going.
Nice shirt, Terry.
Holland?
Canada
Sorry. (but I'll take it as a yes)
I look forward to when he says "YES" I will see ya on the river in December.
Ya wany i should send ya back  some of those baits you sent me They catch bigger fish than that one Nice fish Terry!!!! Snapping turtles are OOS Brian
Made for a great soup Paul.
Don't worry Brian, I've already reported you.
Right ON Terry bud!!!  On 'em large!!!  Brian CMON MAN!  WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU!!!
I didnt post a photo,of the OOS turtle and a pic of the soup. CASE CLOSED.
I,ll get back on track Drew,once we hit smallie waters.
I also don't have your address, full name, licence plate or any other info on you. I guess I could say creepy guy with a moustache who lives in barrie!
See how great a poacher I am.  Even you cant catch me. lm mis spelled
I believe that snapping turtles are the only turtle in Ontario that you can capture and consume legally if you have a licence.
I am fully aware of that Rob. My stringer, is just getting yanked by a young gun.    Seams to have a marsh theme to it.
